    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAMBER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0201009" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAMBER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_3.xml" xrefid="hl0201001">WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTMENT</hotlnk>, steps 1 and 2.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjustment is made by the addition or subtraction of shims between the upper kingpin bracket
                and spindle yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201012">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201012.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Positioning Camber Adjustment Shim</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the four bolts at the upper kingpin bracket, loosening the bracket from the spindle
                yoke. Remove only the top two bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove or install shims as necessary to achieve the desired camber (refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201012">Figure 12</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201013">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201013" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201013.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Adding Camber Adjustment Shims</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Typical setting is 1/2&#176; positive, accomplished by factory installation of a shim
                between the upper kingpin bracket and the spindle yoke. Consult a tire specialist for specific
                recommendations.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-install bolts and tighten to 175 ft-lbs. (235 N&#183;m).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
